* - Children routes-
--Children routes let you nest pages inside other pages, so you can organize your site better and reuse layouts.
-- for example-
Imagine a website as a book:

The main chapters are your main routes (like Home, About, Contact).
Sometimes, a chapter has its own sections or sub-chapters. These are the children routes.
# 2 types of routing in web apps

Client-side routing = handled in the browser, no full page reloads.
Server-side routing = handled on the server, full page reloads for each navigation.
* functional component and class based component-
FUNCTIONAL COMPONENT-
A functional component in React is a JavaScript function that returns React elements (JSX) to render UI. Unlike class components, functional components are simpler and do not use the class keyword. They can accept props as arguments and, with React hooks (like useState and useEffect), can manage state and side effects.
Functional components are just functions.
They return JSX.
They can use hooks for state and lifecycle features.
They are the recommended way to write components in modern React.
* CLASS BASED COMPONENT-
A class-based component in React is a component defined using a JavaScript ES6 class that extends React.Component. It must include a render() method that returns JSX. Class components can hold their own state and use lifecycle methods (like componentDidMount, componentDidUpdate, componentWillUnmount) to run code at specific points in the component’s life.
Uses class syntax and extends React.Component.
Has a render() method that returns JSX.
Can manage state with this.state and update it with this.setState().
Can use lifecycle methods for side effects.
Before React hooks, class components were required for state and lifecycle logic. Now, functional components with hooks are preferred.
* - SINGLE RESPONSIBILITY PRINCIPLE
Every part of your code (like a function, class, or module) should have only one job or reason to change.
In code, this makes programs easier to understand, test, and maintain. If you need to change how one thing works, you only have to update one place, not many.
* -CUSTOM HOOK-
CA custom hook in React is a way to reuse logic across different components. Think of it like a recipe: if you have a set of steps you often repeat (like fetching data, handling forms, or managing timers), you can put those steps into a custom hook. Then, whenever you need that logic, you just "call" the custom hook in your component, instead of rewriting the same code.
Custom hooks make your code cleaner, easier to maintain, and help avoid repeating yourself.
* - LAZY LOADING
Lazy loading means loading something only when it’s actually needed, instead of loading everything at the very beginning.
In React, lazy loading is often used to load components only when they are needed, making your app faster and more efficient.


